You may have been close with using the `@EnableConfigurationProperties` annotation because Spring did not know how to map the properties from your file to the class.
Have a look at the examples from [the docs](https://docs.spring.io/spring-boot/docs/current/reference/html/features.html#features.external-config.typesafe-configuration-properties.constructor-binding). Each dot implies the nesting of the properties.

To be able to do it you can change the `PasswordConfig` so that it corresponds with the password.properties structure:

```java
@Configuration
@EnableConfigurationProperties(PasswordConfig.class)
@Log4j2
@Validated
@ConfigurationProperties
@Setter
@PropertySource(&quot;classpath:password.properties&quot;)
public class PasswordConfig {

    private Range length;
    private Character character;

    @Setter
    @ToString
    static class Character {
        private MinBoxed digit;
        private MinBoxed lowercase;
        private MinBoxed uppercase;
        private MinBoxed special;
    }

    @Setter
    @ToString
    static class Range {
        @Min(1)
        private Integer max;
        @Min(1)
        private Integer min;
    }

    @Setter
    @ToString
    static class MinBoxed {
        @Min(1)
        private Integer min;
    }

    @Bean
    public PasswordValidator passwordValidator() throws IOException {
        log.info(&quot;Password validator [LENGTH: {}-{}, NUMBERS: {}, LOWERCASE: {}, UPPERCASE: {}, SPECIAL: {}]&quot;, length.min,
                length.max, character.digit.min, character.lowercase.min, character.uppercase.min, character.special.min
        );

        return new PasswordValidator(List.of(
                new LengthRule(length.min, length.max),
                new CharacterRule(EnglishCharacterData.Digit, character.digit.min),
                new CharacterRule(EnglishCharacterData.LowerCase, character.lowercase.min),
                new CharacterRule(EnglishCharacterData.UpperCase, character.uppercase.min),
                new CharacterRule(EnglishCharacterData.Special, character.special.min),
                new WhitespaceRule()
        ));
    }
}
```
Additional notes: 
 1. In your original snippet the `LengthRule` parameters should be flipped
 2. You can use `@AllArgsConstructor` annotation istead of `@Setter`. You have to combine it with the `@ConstructorBinding` annotation. For example for the Character nested class:
```java
    @ConstructorBinding
    @AllArgsConstructor
    @ToString
    static class Character {
        private MinBoxed digit;
        private MinBoxed lowercase;
        private MinBoxed uppercase;
        private MinBoxed special;
    }
```

